				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The issue with windows not finding itself has to do with which partition its placed on, not with which bootloader you use.  If you didn't configure your bootloader properly, thats a whole different issue.
<br />

<br />
Now, if you install windows after lumix, windows definately WILL overwrite the master boot record, all you need to do to fix it is boot from any unix disk, chroot your linux partition, and rerun grub or lilo.<br />_________________<br />Even as much of the Internet has come to resemble a pleasant, well-policed suburb, a little-known neighborhood known as Internet Relay Chat remains the Wild West</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
