			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would like to take this opportunity to pimp Ion ( <a href="http://modeemi.cs.tut.fi/~tuomov/ion/" target="_blank">http://modeemi.cs.tut.fi/~tuomov/ion/</a> ), which is nothing but pure sex.
<br />

<br />
Ion is a tiling, tabbing window manager which lets no screen real estate go to waste.
<br />

<br />
Ion is really a new paradigm, rather than just a different way to launch apps; Ion changes the way that windows behave and are placed.
<br />

<br />
basically when you start Ion you have a blank frame and a blank workspace.  You can split the frame into two with hotkeys, either horizontally or vertically, and you can have an infinate number of workspaces, switching between them with keys (each workspace takes up a full screen).  Then you can resize your frames.
<br />

<br />
Each frame has an infinite number of tabs.
<br />

<br />
Launching a program will put it in its own tab in the frame that has focus.    
<br />

<br />
Of course you can switch between tabs, frames, and workspaces with easy hotkeys.  
<br />

<br />
And its completely scriptable in Lua, which I haven't bothered to learn yet because the default setting rocks.
<br />

<br />
Load time is nothing short of instantly.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As you can see from the top left frame, I've already been trolling LQ about it:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.msstate.edu/~kwp13/ion.png" target="_blank" class="postlink">click click</a><br />_________________<br />Even as much of the Internet has come to resemble a pleasant, well-policed suburb, a little-known neighborhood known as Internet Relay Chat remains the Wild West</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
